prompt:
Add a public function called StringLength to Calculator.calr that returns the length of a string. It takes str parameter s and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor string operation syntax:
§F{f003:StringLength:pub}
  §I{str:s}
  §O{i32}
  §R (len s)
§/F{f003}

The string operation functions:
- (len s) - returns the length of string s
- (upper s) - converts to uppercase
- (lower s) - converts to lowercase
- These are built-in Calor functions for string manipulation
